<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Opening (pickup-M2): light G 3-note LH; 2-note RH; quick harmonic passing tones ②①⑤
- M3-4 (C→G→D): ④ C full 4-note LH; ① G; ⑤ D alternation — waltz-like flow
- M5-6 (D sustained): ⑤ D4-note bass creates long pedal under melody
- M7 (D→C#°): ⑦° C#° chromatic (C#2-G2-E3-B3) — dissonant approach back to ①
- M8 (D): ⑤ "33" A4-D5-F#5 RH — bright arrival
- M9 (G→C): fast inner voice passing C→E5 on eighth notes
- M11 (Am→G→Bm→D): all four chords in measure — 8th-note harmonic rhythm
- M13 (C→Am→G): ④ full LH C3-G3-E3-C4 — approach to final
- M15 (G→D7): ⑤7 D7 full bass D2-A2-C3-F#3 — final dominant before close
- M16: ① "334" G-D-G-B LH, G4-B4-D5-G5 RH — restful 3/4 close

VOICE LEADING:
- M1→2: D5 common tone RH ①→① across measures
- M9: B4 common between ①→④ measures
- M11: sixteenth-note "slide" through Am→G→Bm→D each with own voicing
- Pedal bass steps faithfully: G→A→G→D→D→G→D→G sequence throughout

TEXTURE ARC:
- Light 3/4 opening — breathes between beats
- M5-6: Sustained D — broad, held pedal feel
- M7: Dissonant C#° — brief chromatic tension
- M8-10: Begins to grow — 3-note RH reaches D5
- M11-12: Most active passage — four chords/measure
- M15-16: Closing — D7 tension resolves to G "334" with pedal
-->
